description: On the run from the cops, the Sire faces life or death decisions as he faces off against the Siphon once again. Only this time, it's for KEEPS. Featuring a brilliant cover by superstar Tyler Kirkham.

Heidi prepares to trudge through the freak blizzard to take on the Ice Princess. But first she takes a visit to Ilsa's house to discover the sad truth behind Princess' father. What Heidi discovers will make her confrontation with the Ice Princess all the more difficult.

Heidi finally gets to talk to her secret crush Jack about life, love, and their superpowers. Meanwhile, Marcus has what may be the worst day of his life. Will Heidi be there to help her friend, or will she be too busy with Jack to notice?

Britain is destroyed. The U.S. Military is trying to re-build the island. Someone in their ranks has their sights on Selena. Can Clint and Selena survive the Infected while also being hunted down by a rogue agent?

Spookgirl is one tough babe! Her real name is Trixie McGillicutty, an expert on all things supernatural, monstrous, and ooky, and she travels the globe gathering information on the paranormal for a mysterious, unnamed employer -- and to satisfy her own, more personal agenda. And, hey, don't worry about Spookgirl; while she's all cute and cuddly in her Capri pants, she can fight like nobody's business.
name: Issue Name

Chris Lightfellow knows the horror of war--her father died in battle when she was just a little girl. Now, wanting to become a soldier like him, she enters a military school and becomes a knight after graduating. When her commanding officer is killed in the line of duty, Chris shows her fellow knights her true strength--in every war, a hero must rise out of the destructive ashes to usher in the peace!
name: Vol. 1

description: The Karaya clan takes refuge in the caves of the Lizard clan, and Lucia learns about the mysterious assassination of Zepon, the Lizard clan leader. She is relieved when Hugo safely returns after his dangerous mission. However, he has come back with vigor and resolve: He wants to avenge the death of his friend!
name: Vol. 2

description: In their ongoing search for the Flame Champion, Geddoe and his companions come to the village of bug users' community that once belonged to the Grasslands. There, Aila befriends a girl who wants to hear about the Grasslands. Meanwhile, Geddoe crosses paths with a strange cat that speaks to him...but what the cat says Geddoe may not want to hear!
name: Vol. 3

description: Deep in the forest, Chris and Nash venture to the village of the Alma Kinan clan. Once there, Chris meets the spirit medium Yun, who has the ability to see the future, and has insight into Chris and her father. However, Yun is about to be sacrificed by the Alma Kinan in order to open a sacred seal. Will Chris be able to discover what lies ahead before her past is sealed for good?
name: Vol. 4

description: During the fight between Yuber and Geddoe, Hugo takes hold of the fire crest, which binds the power of the crest to him and makes him the "Flame Champion." As the two armies of Karaya and Harmonia converge on the battlefield, will the "Flame Champion" be able to turn the tide of war?
name: Vol. 5

description: The Grasslands and the Zexen Federation have joined forces in the face of Holy Harmonia's onslaught--but the long years of discord between the two have cast a deep shadow over their alliance. Meanwhile, in the ruins of the water of truth, a father and daughter's tearful--reunion and farewell --approaches!
name: Vol. 6

description: The embattled Grasslanders badly need a victory, and for that they need a champion. But is Hugo up to the task? Meanwhile, Chris Lightfellow returns to Zexen...but how will the True Water Rune and the loss of her father affect her duties as Knight Captain? Finally, as intricate machinations inside the Harmonian forces are revealed, death stalks another Rune Bearer--but who will it be?
name: Vol. 7

description: Everything seems to be going smoothly when Hugo awakes, but the arrival of the Zexen Knights to the Grasslander's base marks the first signs of trouble. Meanwhile, the strains between Chris and Hugo's relationship are pushed deeper as questions about the relationship between Chris and the chieftain of the Lizard Clan brought to light. Nonetheless, they are forced to be comrades-at-arms and a bond may reduce the bad blood between the two when Chris confronts Hugo about her father.
name: Vol. 8

description: Franz, the bug-soldier leader, is arrested and sentenced. A big battle ensues between Zexen and Grasslanders versus the encroaching Harmonians. In the midst of the battle, Hugo comes face to face with Luke at last! The two groups go up against an unknown, but it's certain to end in a disastrous battle whose outcome hangs on Hugo's actions. Just like The Water Margin...? Well, not exactly, but fun nonetheless.
name: Vol. 9

description: As the mysterious Harmonian renegade troops begin a secret ceremony that may bring about the end of the world, Thomas's Chateau secretly meets with Lord Sasarai. Hugo is torn by a sacred relic slowly devouring his soul--he is snatched away by the Harmonian renegades, only to be confronted later by an unexpected acquaintance...
name: Vol. 10

description: It's the grand finale for Suikoden III, and the bearers of the True Water, Lightning and Fire Runes must face ghosts from their past during the ultimate shodown! Sasarai arrives to battle his twin, and suddenly the fight is four against one, but when Luc's Rune goes berserk, the balance between the forces of order and the instruments of chaos goes wildly awry. But does it all even matter if Hugo cannot show his might when it really counts?
name: Vol. 11

description: Hina is an innocent young schoolgirl, straightforward and honest with her feelings. When a new neighbor moves in next door, she is instantly drawn to him, although he seems to be aloof. The next day at school, her new neighbor turns out to be her new substitute teacher, Aso Shiro. His presence creates a commotion at the all-girls school. Hina likes the simple things in life . holding hands, hugging cats, walking home together, etc. And being able to experience these things with Aso fills Hina with a warm fuzzy feeling--is this love?
name: Vol. 1

description: Book-smart but street-hopeless Hina is making friends with her crush/teacher/next door neighbor Aso-sensei--whether he likes it or not! Or is she...? Unbeknownst to Hina, Aso is not the mild-mannered teacher he appears to be. In fact, he has just escaped a sordid past, is on a top secret 'job' right now...and his target seems to be Hina! Hina's friends distrust his willingness to spend time with her. And sketchy author Tomoaki Aso's former acquaintance and Hina's new 'friend' appears to be watching both of them with great interest. Meanwhile, Hina is starting to get phone calls with no one on the other end...footprints in her flower garden and items in her house completely rearranged. Can Aso-sensei keep her out of danger...or is being with him the greatest danger of all?
name: Vol. 2

description: Hinata Asahi is the happiest girl you'd ever hope to meet. What's most remarkable is that she's kept that upbeat personality after having been the victim of multiple kidnappings. Ever since her new homeroom teacher, Shiro Asou, moved in next door, Hina's all but forgotten her traumatic past--after all, she's in love with Asou-sensei! But when your dad is as wealthy as Hina's is, the threat of kidnapping doesn't go away...and, in fact, it's about to catch up with Hina one last time...
name: Vol. 3

description: In the world of the Exorcist Underground, the fourth grader Hibiki summons Shikigami to fight for the safety of mankind. Along with being a normal schoolgirl and battling dangerous spirits called Ayakashi, Hibiki has also been tasked with finding six magical jewels that will make her the next leader of the Exorcists! But with fumbling friends, giant evil spiders, and fanatical rivals, it looks like her quest will be less than easy...
name: Vol. 1

description: Xamot’s wild, unbridled actions have come under the gaze of the Commander, as is evident when all of his clearance is suddenly revoked. Tomax, on the other hand, still retains what little power the Paoli’s have, and stays in the Commander’s good graces. All of this proves to be a façade however, a bid by Xamot to take control of Cobra, a coup. Xamot subdues and replaces Tomax, assaults a unit of Vipers, and creates chaos, framing Chuckles in the process. However, the Commander was aware of Xamot’s plan and placed Chuckles in his path, a promise to the former Joe that he would get revenge on his enemy. In that final moment, Chuckles declares his true allegiance and assassinates the Commander, fulfilling his original mission. As Chuckles fights one of the Crimson Guard, Xamot escapes. Chuckles promises to destroy ever Cobra between himself and the door.
name: Rattler

description:
Chicago 1938-Britt Reid has been the Green Hornet for four or five months now and have just struck a huge blow to Caruso's crime family. Caruso is angry and believes the Green Hornet maybe working withe Irish mob, and after the Hornet attacks one of Caruso's transportation hubs, Caruso calls a meeting. At the meeting Caruso guns down the Irish mob's head bosses.

Four Months Earlier- Britt Reid is forced to sell his family home to purchase the property that will become the Hornet's Nest.

These are the chronicles of Tony Stark: the playboy, the genius inventor, the philanthropist, the director of S.H.I.E.L.D., the futurist, the hero. This handbook is the definitive resource to the world of Iron Man, featuring Tony's closest allies (Happy and Pepper Hogan, War Machine, the Order) and deadliest foes (Justin Hammer, Mandarin, Obadiah Stane)! Includes a complete gallery of the Iron Man armors, and all-new schematics of key armors and the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier! Also featuring 1993's original Iron Manual, plus unrevealed armor concepts from the Iron Man/Force Works Collector's Preview. Collecting THE IRON MANUAL, THE ALL-NEW IRON MANUAL and Material from THE IRON MAN/FORCE WORKS COLLECTOR'S PREVIEW.

When Squadron Strange accept a mission from a ghost, they find themselves on their most perilous raid ever... straight into the heart of a haunted mansion! Sgt. Rufus Whedon and Corporal Bode Locke have a terrifying lesson to learn: if you're dealing with a dead man, you better think fast and fight hard, if you don't want to wind up one yourself!
name: Casualties

volume.name: Locke & Key: Keys to the Kingdom

description: Ratchet and Clank's desperate gamble to save Veldin and the entire galaxy meets with partial success, except they find themselves hunted on a frozen planet for the key to the entire Helios Project – an ancient comet shard. Can the pair survive long enough to use the shard to put the galaxy right?!
name: Multiple Organisms

description: Roscoe Kalashnikov was sure he could get away with murder – and in a town as corrupt as Central City, maybe he could. But if that’s so, why do his victim’s words still haunt him? She said something about “the spirit of justice” and now, around every corner, Roscoe is seeing a flash of trench coat and the briefest glimpse of a masked man…
name: Crime and Punishment

description: Jetfire makes his final judgment against humanity, as he comes face to face with Sector 7 founder Walter Simmons! Meanwhile, in Sector 7's Arctic Command, still housing the frozen frame of Megatron, someone has turned traitor ... or is there a Decepticon in their midst? All the answers are here, as the lead-up to TRANSFORMERS III heats up!
name: Frozen

description: Sara Pezzini has investigated countless bizarre crimes, but her latest case may be the most shocking yet! Pezzini and her detective partner have encountered monsters and demons before, but these latest supernatural terrors seem to be born from the imagination of an innocent child.
name: Paper Monsters, Part 2

description: The Shadowplague continues! Fell's Five descends into the ruins of a lost dwarven stead, uncovering an ancient secret: dark experiments in magic that the dwarves would rather leave buried. Join us as John Rogers and Andrea Di Vito forge ahead with their thrilling adventures of swords and sorcery.
name: Shadowplague, Part Three: A Series of Very Bad Plans

description: The legendary John Byrne brings his talents to the world of Jurassic Park and the results have never been more terrifying! Sheriff Tobias suddenly has more on his plate than he can handle when he is confronted with numerous cattle mutilations and the disappearance of a local farmer. Tensions escalate as the Feds arrive on the scene and the mysterious predators make their presence known!

volume.name: Jurassic Park: The Devils in the Desert

We step back a moment to detail the appearances of two key characters in the WHEEL OF TIME saga: The Peddler and The Gleeman. Edmond's Field, while preparing for the annual Bel Tine Festival, receives two more very important guests. One is Padan Fain, the peddler who travels from town to town in his wagon, bringing goods to trade as well as news and rumors from abroad, including one of war and a false Dragon. The other is gleeman Thom Merrilin, arriving in his patchwork cloak, ready to entertain and thrill the crowds with his song and dance. Both are not as they appear, and soon will be swept up into events neither could foresee...
name: The Peddler and The Gleeman

description: Jon Moore is the most demanded spy-for-hire in Europe's criminal under- world. This is due in large part because of Jake Ellis, a psychic man who is invisible to everyone except Moore. When a deal goes bad, the only one who can protect Moore from Europe's most dangerous criminals is Jake Ellis. No one but Moore can see Jake Ellis, but Jake Ellis is aware of everything.
name: Are You Listening?
Ultimate Annuals Return
New Avengers #1

description:
Asgard's in shambles, Odin's not who he seems, and Enrakt the Enchanter has been following the thunder god far more closely than suspected! Thor also faces earthly foes in the Absorbing Man, Titania and the unstoppable Juggernaut!

Collects Thor #14-17, Iron Man #21-22, Peter Parker: Spider-Man #11 & Juggernaut: The Eighth Day.

Collects Thor #14-17, Iron Man #21-22, Peter Parker Spider Man #11 and Juggernaut: The Eighth Day
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Thor By Dan Jurgens & John Romita Jr.

description:
As his classic run continues, Dan Jurgens introduces new threats for the God of Thunder to face, and the stakes are higher than ever! Thanos has gathered artifacts that threaten Earth's very existence, and he's got the all-powerful Mangog at his side! Thor, Odin and the Scarlet Witch battle Enrakt the Enchanter in another dimension! Plus: Loki! Mephisto! And is Jake Olson a murderer? Guest-starring the Warriors Three, Sif, Balder and Firelord!

Collects Thor (1998) #18-25, Annual 2000.
name: Volume 4

volume.name: Thor By Dan Jurgens & John Romita Jr.

name: The Teen Wonder

description: Don't miss this new collection featuring stories of different Batmen from BATMAN: LEGENDS OF THE DARK KNIGHT #168, BATMAN #666, BATMAN BEYOND #1, BATMAN #512, DETECTIVE COMICS #665 and TEEN TITANS #18.
name: Under the Cowl

description: Green Arrow provides the focal point for two stories set early in the careers of Batman, Green Lantern and the Emerald Archer in this volume that collects LEGENDS OF THE DC UNIVERSE #7-9 and LEGENDS OF THE DARK KNIGHT #127-131. Writer Dennis O'Neil contributes an introduction.
name: The Ring, the Arrow and the Bat

plus excerpts from Shadowhawk Gallery (1994) #1

The stories and artwork that laid the groundwork for the most successful independent comic book ever published. SPAWN: ORIGINS, VOL. 1 includes the introduction of not only Spawn, but also a number of other memorable and menacing characters, including Malebolgia, Overtkill and the Violator.

The first Spawn: Origins issue, reprinting Spawn #1-6.
name: Volume 1
Reborn
The Captain Is Back

description: The Gamekeeper just wanted to be left alone and to forget about his dark past. But now it has come back to haunt him, forcing him to confront a secret that has remained buried for over a decade. A secret that men have already killed for.
Why must Elisa turn to Xanatos for help? And what could make the Gargoyles' asch-villain their ally?
name: Into the Future

description: Jebediah “Hellrider” Foster’s dark outlaw past continues to consume any hopes he has of a brighter future with his new wife as they await the impending birth of their first child. In Silent Hill, there is always a price to pay for evil, and sometimes it’s the innocent who suffer more than the truly guilty.

The deeds from Hellrider's past has now come home to roost. With memories flooding through the whiskey, Jebediah's evil ways come to claim his soul. With Esther giving birth, Jebediah struggles to reach her. In the end, was it just the whiskey doing its work, or was it something more that came to extract its vengeance.
